section.para:
			Open a CoNLL-U sample stream, train a model, and parse tokens with their
			part-of-speech tags:

ObjectStream<DependencySample> samples =
    new ConlluDependencySampleStream(conlluInput, ConlluTagset.U);

TrainingParameters parameters = TrainingParameters.defaultParams();
parameters.put(Parameters.CUTOFF_PARAM, 0);
DependencyModel model = DependencyParserME.train("eng", samples, parameters);
DependencyParserME parser = new DependencyParserME(model);

DependencyGraph graph = parser.parse(
    new String[] {"the", "dog", "barks"},
    new String[] {"DET", "NOUN", "VERB"});
// graph.headOf(0) == 1, graph.relationOf(0) == "det"
// graph.root() is the index of the root token

			A trained model serializes like any other tool model. Evaluation accumulates
			unlabeled and labeled attachment scores through
			DependencyEvaluator.
